                    }
                  ],
                  "unit_combination": "(%)"
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The 56Fe(n,n'gamma)56Fe reaction was finally studied at",
                "a neutron energy of 2.5 MeV, in order to obtain",
                "absolute normalisation by comparing the gamma-yields",
                "from the sample with the known values for the 90.degr.",
                "differential production cross sections of the 846 and",
                "1240 keV gamma-rays."
              ]
            }
